Reasoning: 
1. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper proposes a design of random access memory using reversible logic, which is an emerging technology in the field of digital design. 
2. cs.AR (Architecture): The paper discusses the design of a reversible decoder and a write enable reversible master slave D flip-flop, which are architectural components of the reversible random access memory. 
3. cs.DC (Digital Circuits): The paper deals with the design of digital circuits for the reversible random access memory. 
4. cs.EM (Electromagnetics): The paper may involve electromagnetic considerations in the design of the reversible random access memory. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may discuss the computational complexity of the proposed reversible designs compared to the existing designs in literature.
